From: Felix Fietkau <nbd@nbd.name>
Date: Tue, 26 Aug 2025 22:04:57 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] nl80211: fix reporting spurious frame events

When the nl80211 driver is shared across multiple interfaces (on the same
wiphy), nl80211_spurious_frame can send the event to the wrong interface by
using drv->ctx. Fix this by using bss->ctx instead.

This is upstream OpenWrt commit 9c895bacfb ("hostapd: fix wds ap on
single-wiphy devices"), which was dropped by the "hostapd: update to
2026-02-27" version bump and not carried into the newer hostapd snapshot.
Restored locally because the W1700K runs multiple BSSes on a single wiphy
(phy0) and is affected: spurious-frame events are otherwise delivered to
the first BSS, deauthing/kicking clients on the other SSIDs.

Signed-off-by: Felix Fietkau <nbd@nbd.name>
---

--- a/src/drivers/driver_nl80211_event.c
+++ b/src/drivers/driver_nl80211_event.c
@@ -2804,5 +2804,5 @@ static void nl80211_spurious_frame(struc
 	event.rx_from_unknown.link_id = tb[NL80211_ATTR_MLO_LINK_ID] ?
 		nla_get_u8(tb[NL80211_ATTR_MLO_LINK_ID]) : -1;
 
-	wpa_supplicant_event(drv->ctx, EVENT_RX_FROM_UNKNOWN, &event);
+	wpa_supplicant_event(bss->ctx, EVENT_RX_FROM_UNKNOWN, &event);
 }
